Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: smart-pca
Version: 0.1.2
Summary: PCA with varimax rotation and feature selection compatible with scikit-learn
Home-page: https://github.com/electronsz
Author: Electronsz
Author-email: janetuker2@gmail.com
License: MIT
Project-URL: Source Code, https://github.com/electronsz/advanced-principle-component-analysis
Project-URL: Documentation, https://pypi.org/project/advanced-pca/#description
Description: Researchers use Principle Component Analysis (PCA) intending to summarize features, identify structure in data or reduce the number of features. The interpretation of principal components is challenging in most of the cases due to the high amount of cross-loadings (one feature having significant weight across many principal components). Different types of matrix rotations are used to minimize cross-loadings and make factor interpretation easier.
Keywords: Principle Component Analysis,Matrix rotation,Feature selection,PCA,scikit-learn
